-- Iberia Express to Offer 17 Summer Routes, Build 14-Plane Fleet
-- B y   C h r i s   J a s p e r
-- 2012-03-23T15:10:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/iberia-express-to-offer-17-summer-routes-build-14-plane-fleet.html
Iberia Express, the new domestic
unit of International Consolidated Airlines Group SA’s Spanish
arm, will operate 17 routes in the summer season and end the
first year with 14 aircraft and 500 workers, it said today.  Iberia Express commences flights on March 25 with an
initial four planes operating between  Madrid , Palma de
Majorca, Alicante, Malaga and Seville, accordin to a statement.  IAG formed the lower-cost unit to restore’s Iberia’s short-
and medium-haul routes to profitability. Five of the planned
routes will be to destinations beyond  Spain  and its islands.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Jasper at 
 cjasper@bloomberg.net  